metadata.name: Underwater by Veronika Szendro
metadata.description:
“I plunge into a dark space. My body is drifted by the streams. I am groping in the dark. This is how we are ‘swimming’ through our life without knowing where we are coming from and where we are going to.”

The artist, researcher and founder of Art of Future was born (1990) in Szeged (HUN) . She studied at the University of Pecs Faculty of Art (HUN). In addition, she attends the Doctoral School of Art at University of Pécs and participated at an exchange program at Yale Divinity School (New Haven, CT) for a semester. She exhibited in group exhibitions in London (GB), Chicago (USA), Stockholm (SWE), Milan (IT), Saint Petersburg (RU) and Barcelona (SP).
